{{Infobox video game | title = Canadian Football 2017 | developer = Canuck Play Inc. | publisher = Canuck Play Inc. | engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]] | platforms = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Xbox One]] | released = {{Video game release|NA|July 26, 2017}} | genre = [[Sports game|Sports]] | designer = David Winter }}
'''''Canadian Football 2017''''' is a [[gridiron football]] [[video game]] developed by [[Peterborough, Ontario]]-based Canuck Play, a team led by David Winter, a former [[EA Sports]] developer previously behind ''[[Maximum Football]]'' and ''[[CFL Football '99]]''. The game uses [[Canadian football]] rules, but is not officially licensed by either the [[Canadian Football League]] or [[Canadian Football League Players' Association|the players' association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2017/07/25/cfl-fans-finally-have-video-game--kind-of|title=CFL Blitz: Fans finally have a CFL video game ... kind of|first=Gerry|last=Moddejonge|work=[[Toronto Sun]]|publisher=[[Postmedia Network]]|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 25, 2017}}</ref>
The game was released on July 26, 2017 on [[Microsoft Windows]] and [[Xbox One]]. A [[PlayStation 4]] version is currently in development.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://3downnation.com/2017/03/19/interview-canadian-football-video-game-almost-ready-launch/|title=Interview: Canadian football video game almost ready for launch|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=July 25, 2017|work=3 Down Nation|first=Santino|last=Filoso}}</ref> As of March 2018, the PS4 version has yet to release.
